{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Audit and Fix i18n Translations in Hugo Templates\n\nComplete a comprehensive audit of internationalization (i18n) usage across all Hugo templates, identify missing translation keys for English and Polish locales, and add the missing translations.\n\nRequirements:\n- Scan all Hugo template files (.html files in layouts/, themes/*/layouts/, partials/, shortcodes/) for i18n function calls\n- Extract all translation keys being referenced (look for patterns like `i18n \"key\"`, `T \"key\"`, or similar Hugo i18n syntax)\n- Generate a complete list of unique translation keys required by the templates\n- Compare extracted keys against existing translation files (i18n/en.toml, i18n/en.yaml, i18n/pl.toml, i18n/pl.yaml, or similar)\n- Identify keys that exist in templates but are missing from English translation file\n- Identify keys that exist in templates but are missing from Polish translation file\n- Add missing translation entries to both en and pl translation files with appropriate translations\n- Ensure translation file format and structure matches existing conventions\n- Verify no duplicate keys exist in translation files\n- Document the complete list of found keys and which ones were added",
